Rating: 3
Very delicious. I agree with the earlier reviewer, saute the scallions with the mustard seeds. My wife really liked it, after a lot of hesitation because she thought it sounded "weird". We served this with baked salmon ala Simbajak. We slather dijon mustard on the salmon, then cover with a heaping of brown sugar, bake or broil. Now we have "Mustard Night" at our household.

Rating: 4
Delicious! Even my two-year-old ate this. The second time I made it, I sauteed the chopped scallions in the hot oil after adding the mustard seeds and everybody who tried it agreed that this was even better than mixing them in raw at the end, as the recipe calls for.